<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by lar on 08-27-2000 07:31 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hmmm, you know, on occasion, you are walking through steppes of grass, and then there aren't that much trees in the neighborhood.  I mean, it's a large world, and it is rather normal if you ask me, that there are open areas. When talking about that particular location we are east of Rivertown, just left some farmers lands, not far from the main route to Verdistis. It's not because Diablo managed to put you for hours against a grass background, that we should avoid the grass fields, right ? It fits to the topology of the area you're in - wouldn't make sense at all to have forests there, and we do have some forests  ;)If you would move a little bit more to the west from where that shot was taken, you would btw have stumbled about a burnt out farm.

As for the reflections, and I quote the council here, "The apprentice may have noted that when he casts a spell, its manifestation in our realm will be invisible when looking at in a mirror. This is due to the higher planar nature of magic, a matter which will be addressed in future lessons"  ;)

And yes, I know skeletons don't bleed. I'll never do it again  ;)

Lar

Lar


